Summary_en:
With the USD/KRW at 1,471.32 KRW (intraday 1,467.90–1,477.18 KRW), the Won has clearly shifted to a stronger trend compared to the previous week's high of 1,490.12 KRW (April 29). The Won is being supported as South Korea’s April exports exceeded $80 billion (for the second consecutive month) and the trade surplus recorded over $20 billion. Since the Won entering a strong phase can be utilized as a timing for negotiating imported raw materials, we will review increasing the proportion of negotiations after confirming whether the rate stabilizes below 1,470 KRW within this week.

① Increase the proportion of dollar negotiations if the rate stabilizes below 1,470 KRW this week (Deadline: This week);

② Frequently monitor the progress of US-Iran peace negotiations in the Middle East (Deadline: As needed);

③ Re-examine the forward exchange hedge ratio if the dollar weakness persists (Deadline: Within May).

Summary:
시카고 연준 굴스비 총재가 5월 3일(토) 인터뷰에서 '최근 인플레이션 지표는 나쁜 소식'이라 발언. 3월 <b>PCE(개인소비지출) 물가 전년비 +3.5%</b>로 상승세 지속, 관세·에너지 영향 없는 서비스 물가도 동반 상승 중. CME FedWatch 기준 6월 금리 인하 확률 <b>10% 미만</b>으로 급감. <mark>연준 금리 동결 장기화 → 달러 강세 지속 시나리오 대비, 수입 부품·원자재의 달러 결제 비중과 환헤지 전략을 즉시 재점검해야 한다.</mark>
 ①달러 강세 시나리오 대비 선물환 헤지 비중 점검(기한: 5월 내);
 ②6월 FOMC(6월 11~12일) 결과 모니터링(기한: 6월 중);
 ③원자재 달러 결제 비중 분산 방안 검토(기한: 분기 내).

Summary_en:
Chicago Fed President Goolsby stated in an interview on Saturday, May 3, that "recent inflation indicators are bad news." March PCE (Personal Consumption Expenditures) prices continued their upward trend at +3.5% year-over-year, and service prices, unaffected by tariffs and energy, are also rising in tandem. According to CME FedWatch, the probability of a June rate cut has plummeted to less than 10%. In preparation for a scenario where the Fed maintains a frozen interest rate and the dollar remains strong, the proportion of dollar settlements for imported parts and raw materials, as well as currency hedging strategies, must be immediately re-examined.

① Review the proportion of forward exchange hedges in preparation for a strong dollar scenario (Deadline: Within May);

② Monitor the results of the June FOMC meeting (June 11–12) (Deadline: Mid-June);

③ Review measures to diversify the proportion of dollar settlements for raw materials (Deadline: Within the quarter).

Summary:
4월 28~29일 <b>FOMC 8-4 표결</b>(1992년 이후 최대 분열)로 금리 <b>3.5~3.75%</b> 동결 결정. 미란 총재는 25bp 인하 주장, 해먹·카시카리·로건 총재는 완화 편향 표현에 반대. 파월 의장 임기는 <b>5월 15일 종료</b> 예정으로, 차기 의장 지명 동향 주목. <mark>차기 연준 의장 성향에 따라 금리 경로·달러 환율 방향이 급변할 수 있어, 후임 지명 발표 시 즉각적인 구매 전략 재검토가 필요하다.</mark>
 ①차기 연준 의장 후보 성향 파악(기한: 5월 내);
 ②CME FedWatch 금리 인하 기대 추이 주간 모니터링(기한: 수시);
 ③USD 강세 장기화 시 원자재 헤지 시나리오 수립(기한: 분기 내).

Summary_en:
The FOMC voted 8-4 on April 28–29 (the largest split since 1992), resulting in a decision to keep interest rates frozen at 3.5–3.75%. Governor Miran argued for a 25bp cut, while Governors Hammock, Kashkari, and Logan opposed expressions of dovish bias. With Chairman Powell’s term set to end on May 15, attention is focused on developments regarding the nomination of the next chairman. As the direction of interest rate paths and the dollar exchange rate could shift rapidly depending on the inclination of the next Fed Chairman, an immediate review of purchasing strategies is required upon the announcement of a successor nomination.

① Identify the inclinations of the next Fed Chairman candidates (Deadline: Within May);

② Weekly monitoring of interest rate cut expectations on CME FedWatch (Deadline: As needed);

③ Establish commodity hedging scenarios in case of a prolonged USD strength (Deadline: Within the quarter).

Summary:
미 대법원 <b>IEEPA 관세 위헌 판결(6-3)</b> 이후 CBP가 4월 20일 CAPE Phase 1 시스템 가동, <b>5월 11일</b> 첫 환급 개시 예정. 4월 26일 기준 <b>7만 5,300건</b> CAPE 신청 접수(1,120만 건 이상 Entry 포함), 환급 대상 관세 총액 최대 <b>1,660억 달러</b> 추정. <mark>IEEPA 관세 환급이 본격화되면 미국 내 수입원가 구조가 단기 급변할 수 있어, 대미 수입 부품·소재 품목의 환급 가능 여부를 즉각 확인하고 예산 계획에 반영해야 한다.</mark>
 ①CAPE 신청 대상 품목 법무·관세 팀과 즉시 확인(기한: 즉시);
 ②환급 수령 시 원자재 조달 예산 재검토(기한: 5월 내);
 ③대미 수입 부품의 관세 환급 가능 금액 산정(기한: 2주 내).

Summary_en:
Following the U.S. Supreme Court ruling that IEEPA tariffs were unconstitutional (6-3), CBP launched the CAPE Phase 1 system on April 20 and is scheduled to begin the first refunds on May 11. As of April 26, 75,300 CAPE applications had been received (including over 11.2 million entries), with the total tariffs eligible for refund estimated at up to $166 billion. As the IEEPA tariff refund process begins in earnest, the structure of import costs within the U.S. could undergo rapid short-term changes; therefore, the eligibility for refunds on parts and materials imported from the U.S. must be immediately verified and reflected in budget plans.

① Immediately verify items eligible for CAPE application with the Legal and Customs teams (Deadline: Immediately);

② Review the raw material procurement budget upon receipt of refunds (Deadline: Within May);

③ Calculate the refundable amount for parts imported from the U.S. (Deadline: Within 2 weeks).

The USTR has published a Section 301 investigation in the Federal Register targeting multiple countries that have failed to comply with their obligation to ban the import of products made with forced labor, with a public hearing scheduled for May 5. There is a precedent where Section 301 investigations have led to the imposition of additional tariffs of up to several hundred percent. As there is a risk of additional tariffs if parts and materials suppliers located in China or Southeast Asia fall under the category of countries with forced labor issues, a pre-emptive supply chain review is urgent.

① Immediately verify whether the countries where major suppliers are located fall under forced labor issues (Deadline: Immediately);

② Secure a list of alternative suppliers in advance (Deadline: Within 1 month);

③ Prepare an impact assessment report after verifying the results of the May 5 hearing (Deadline: Second week of May).

